2020-2021 School Calendar






BCISD District News







ATTENTION: 
Dear Brooks County ISD Parents, Students, Stakeholders, and Community, 

In light of the evolving conditions surrounding COVID-19, we continue to take proactive steps to protect the health and well-being of our students, families, staff, and Brooks County community. After careful deliberation with Brooks County Emergency Team, Brooks County ISD Administration and Instructional Leadership Team, we have made the decision to provide virtual and online learning and extend the suspension of normal campus operations through May 4, 2020 
. 

Click picture for full message from the superintendent. 



























FREE LEARNING RESOURCES 


Keep checking back as we continue to build a list of "Free Learning Resources" 
that your children will love doing at home during the coronavirus crisis! 











List of Services 



Brooks County ISD to Provide FREE Curbside Meals to Children 18 and younger 

Brooks County ISD Food Services will offer free curbside meals during the madated school closures. Grab & Go Meals will be available at EVERY bus stop starting at 10am. On Fridays meals will include Saturday and Sunday meals.
Also, meals can be picked up at the Falfurrias Junior High Cafeteria from 9:30am till 1pm each day.









We are a member of the Rural Schools Innovation Zone (RSIZ)! 

The RSIZ is a partnership between three school districts — Brooks County ISD, Freer ISD, and Premont ISD. The partnership includes 4 Academies.
Brooks County's Academy the Ignite Technical Institute, is located at Falfurrias High School. Our Academy is one of four exciting career pathways! .

 Learn more about each RSIZ academy 
 List Item 1 






STAAR Results 

Learn about your child's score on a secure site for parents and/or students to access a student’s state assessment scores for the STAAR, STAAR Alternate 2, and TELPAS programs. www.TexasAssessment.com 

 www.TexasAssessment.com 
 List Item 2 






P-TECH (Pathways in Technology Early College High School) 

The P-TECH at Falfurrias High School will enable our students to begin their college and professional lives more quickly and with more support. Graduates of P-TECH have the opportunity to earn an Applied Associate of Science degree and leave high school with the skills and knowledge they need in order to continue onto a four-year Bachelor's of Applied Science degree, or step seamlessly into competitive, high demand jobs. 

 Read More 









